§ Why ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ We can interpret a real function as tracing a path as we
    move from left to right in its domain.
    † ⦊
      ‖ Future editions will likely have this interpretation in a
        separate sheet. ⦉
    ⦉⦉

  ‖ We want language for whether this tracing increases or
    decreases the range values. ⦉
⦉

§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Let $A ⊂ 𝗥$ and let $f: A → 𝗥$. ⦉

  ‖ A function is ❬monotone increasing❭ if $f(x) < f(y)$
    whenever $x < y$, and ❬monotone nondecreasing❭ if $f(x) ≤
    f(y)$ whenever $x, y ∈ 𝗥$ and $x < y$.
    † ⦊
      ‖ Unforunately, some authors use “monotone increasing for
        “monotone nondecreasing” and use the terminolgy ❬strictly
        monotone increasing❭ for “monotone increasing”.” ⦉
    ⦉⦉

  ‖ Similarly we define ❬monotone decreasing❭ and ❬monotone
    nonincreasing❭. ⦉
⦉

